European Stock-Index Futures Slump Amid Concern Greek Default May Be Close

-- B y   A d a m   H a i g h
-- 
2011-09-12T06:03:34Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-12/european-stock-index-futures-slump-amid-concern-greek-default-may-be-close.html
European stock-index futures
dropped amid speculation  Greece  may be nearing a default on its
sovereign debt, bolstering concern that the crisis will spread
to the banking system.  Futures on the Euro Stoxx 50 Index expiring this month
slumped 2.7 percent to 2,016 at 7:03 a.m. in  London .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Adam Haigh at 
 ahaigh1@bloomberg.net  